arism, modernity, and Americanism—as potent threats to the Catholic precepts that were the true foundations of Italian civilization, values, and culture. The pope and cardinals framed the threat of evangelical Christianity as a peril not only to the Catholic Church but to the fascist government as well, recruiting some very powerful fascist officials to their cause.   This important book is the first full account of this dangerous alliance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aEvangelicalismzItalyxHistory. 0aFascism and the Catholic ChurchzItaly. 0aProtestant churchesxRelationsxCatholic Church. 7aRELIGION / Christian Church / History.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300262889423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300262889.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles